  "text": "Model-fitting the data from perfusion studies using varied 2 values indicated that the estimated bolus durations (ca. 800-1500 ms) and arterial transit times (ca. 550-1000 ms) varied from slice to slice in the cerebellum (Figure 2 ). For the inferior saturation pulse to effectively define the labeled bolus, 1 should be set less than the bolus duration [CITATION_1] ; a 1 of 800 ms was chosen for subsequent optimization studies and quantitative cerebellum CBF estimation using FAIR ASST and PICORE.",
